      "title": "See also"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The probability density for the von Mises distribution is"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "formulas": [
            "p(x) = \\frac{e^{\\kappa cos(x-\\mu)}}{2\\pi I_0(\\kappa)},"
          ],
          "type": "math_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "where "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "\\mu"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is the mode and "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "\\kappa"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " the concentration,\nand "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "I_0(\\kappa)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is the modified Bessel function of order 0."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The von Mises is named for Richard Edler von Mises, who was born in\nAustria-Hungary, in what is now the Ukraine.  He fled to the United\nStates in 1939 and became a professor at Harvard.  He worked in\nprobability theory, aerodynamics, fluid mechanics, and philosophy of\nscience."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "1\n\nAbramowitz, M. and Stegun, I. A. (Eds.). \"Handbook of\nMathematical Functions with Formulas, Graphs, and Mathematical\nTables, 9th printing,\" New York: Dover, 1972.",
          "type": "raw_block"
        },
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "2\n\nvon Mises, R., \"Mathematical Theory of Probability\nand Statistics\", New York: Academic Press, 1964.",
          "type": "raw_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "References"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Draw samples from the distribution:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "mu, kappa = 0.0, 4.0 # mean and concentration"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "s = we.random.vonmises(mu, kappa, 1000)"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Display the histogram of the samples, along with\nthe probability density function:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "from scipy.special import i0  # doctest: +SKIP"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.hist(s, 50, density=True)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "x = we.linspace(-we.pi, we.pi, num=51)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "y = we.exp(kappa*we.cos(x-mu))/(2*we.pi*i0(kappa))  # doctest: +SKIP"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.plot(x, y, linewidth=2, color='r')  # doctest: +SKIP"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.show()"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Examples"
    }
